1
00:00:16,083 --> 00:00:18,666
[KODAI] Why would the enemy care
about this ancient battleship?

2
00:00:18,750 --> 00:00:20,291
[distant aircraft noise]

3
00:00:20,375 --> 00:00:22,125
[SHIMA gasps]

4
00:00:22,208 --> 00:00:24,750
[KODAI gasps]
It's them!

5
00:00:41,041 --> 00:00:44,166
This doesn't make any sense.
Why would they be attacking it?

6
00:00:58,083 --> 00:00:59,041
[FEMALE ANNOUNCEMENT VOICE 2A]
Enemy bombardment

7
00:00:59,125 --> 00:01:00,458
near Cape Bonomisaki.

8
00:01:00,541 --> 00:01:04,208
All personnel, remain
on standby in the shelter.

9
00:01:04,291 --> 00:01:05,625
Are we okay here?

10
00:01:05,708 --> 00:01:07,708
We're supposed to
be launching any day now!

11
00:01:07,791 --> 00:01:10,000
I don't want to die in a tunnel!

12
00:01:12,125 --> 00:01:14,625
What the hell? Where are
they all coming from?

13
00:01:17,458 --> 00:01:19,458
[KODAI gasps]
A carrier.

14
00:01:27,583 --> 00:01:29,166
[ALL yell]

15
00:01:47,916 --> 00:01:49,458
[BOTH gasp]

16
00:01:55,125 --> 00:02:05,083
♪

17
00:02:23,750 --> 00:02:25,416
[SHIMA]
It's the Air Defense Force!

18
00:02:28,208 --> 00:02:29,583
[KATO]
This is Alpha Leader.

19
00:02:29,666 --> 00:02:32,166
Our party guests
have been served the punch.

20
00:02:32,250 --> 00:02:33,666
[MALE UNCF WING DISPATCHER 2A]
Confirmed, Alpha Leader.

21
00:02:33,750 --> 00:02:37,041
Threat has been neutralized.
Return to base.

22
00:02:37,125 --> 00:02:38,583
[KATO]
Roger that.

23
00:02:49,750 --> 00:02:52,291
[KATO sighs]
Idiots.

24
00:02:52,375 --> 00:02:57,666
[SHIMA] Hey, are you kidding me?
Don't leave us here!

25
00:02:57,750 --> 00:03:02,625
[KODAI] She's alive.
This rusted old ship.

26
00:03:13,041 --> 00:03:17,333
[MAN 1 speaking Gamilan]


27
00:03:17,416 --> 00:03:26,625
[speaking Gamilan]


28
00:03:26,708 --> 00:03:29,291
[continues speaking Gamilan]


29
00:03:49,541 --> 00:03:53,541
There. Just don't punch
anything else for a while.

30
00:03:53,625 --> 00:03:57,125
Man. I thought he'd
calmed down. Guess not.

31
00:03:57,208 --> 00:03:59,166
[DR. SADO laughing]

32
00:03:59,250 --> 00:04:01,958
Ah the great joys
of youth, am I right?

33
00:04:02,041 --> 00:04:05,333
You boys did take some radiation
but you should be fine.

34
00:04:05,416 --> 00:04:07,541
Oh, come here, Mew.
I'm not going to be around

35
00:04:07,625 --> 00:04:11,541
for a while. Actually,
you kids won't be either.

36
00:04:11,625 --> 00:04:13,541
Didn't you get
the standby orders, too?

37
00:04:13,625 --> 00:04:15,166
Uh, yeah.

38
00:04:15,250 --> 00:04:16,666
[meows]

39
00:04:16,750 --> 00:04:18,125
[FEMALE EUROPEAN REP. 2A]
The situation is deteriorating,

40
00:04:18,208 --> 00:04:20,875
with energy supplies dwindling
all across the globe.

41
00:04:20,958 --> 00:04:22,375
We're dealing with
famine and riots

42
00:04:22,458 --> 00:04:24,666
in almost every sector,
and poisonous spores

43
00:04:24,750 --> 00:04:27,208
from those alien plants
are still wreaking havoc.

44
00:04:27,291 --> 00:04:29,666
All attempts to curb
the destruction have failed.

45
00:04:29,750 --> 00:04:32,208
Even underground we're
not going to last for long.

46
00:04:32,291 --> 00:04:33,833
That's abundantly clear.

47
00:04:33,916 --> 00:04:35,625
Now that the enemy's
discovered the ship,

48
00:04:35,708 --> 00:04:38,000
how soon can we
execute the launch?

49
00:04:38,083 --> 00:04:39,333
We've moved it up.

50
00:04:39,416 --> 00:04:41,958
We're planning
to embark in 72 hours.

51
00:04:42,041 --> 00:04:44,125
How can you?
I've been told you lost

52
00:04:44,208 --> 00:04:46,708
a great deal of experienced
crewmen in that bombing.

53
00:04:46,791 --> 00:04:50,750
Your information is wrong.
We suffered no casualties.

54
00:04:50,833 --> 00:04:52,250
That's not what we heard either,

55
00:04:52,333 --> 00:04:55,166
but if the hero of the Second
Battle of Mars says it,

56
00:04:55,250 --> 00:04:57,125
I am inclined to believe him.

57
00:04:57,208 --> 00:04:58,583
[SERIZAWA]
Hm!

58
00:04:58,666 --> 00:05:00,750
This plan is being executed
under the UN's authority.

59
00:05:00,833 --> 00:05:03,583
But under the circumstances,
we can't even be there.

60
00:05:03,666 --> 00:05:05,083
The sectors are cut off.

61
00:05:05,166 --> 00:05:08,166
Realistically there's little
we can do to help you now.

62
00:05:08,250 --> 00:05:09,458
[MALE USA REP. 2A]
Same for us.

63
00:05:09,541 --> 00:05:11,208
We're only hanging on
by a thread.

64
00:05:11,291 --> 00:05:14,250
Vice-Admiral,
the Yamato Plan has to succeed,

65
00:05:14,333 --> 00:05:17,083
the hopes of the entire
world are resting on it.

66
00:05:22,791 --> 00:05:31,208
[alarm blaring]

67
00:05:31,291 --> 00:05:41,375
[LAUNCH CONTROLLER 2A
speaking Gamilan]


68
00:05:57,500 --> 00:06:00,041
What is this? You think
we're finally gonna launch?

69
00:06:00,125 --> 00:06:02,666
Must be, that's what the
Izumo Plan's all about, right?

70
00:06:02,750 --> 00:06:05,500
Feels weird leaving
everyone else behind, though.

71
00:06:10,208 --> 00:06:12,625
[OKITA] Soldiers.
The long wait is over.

72
00:06:12,708 --> 00:06:14,375
Each one of you
is here today because

73
00:06:14,458 --> 00:06:17,916
you were selected and trained
for a vital space mission.

74
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:20,041
Now, your mission will commence.

75
00:06:20,125 --> 00:06:23,291
And I will have the honor of
serving as your ship's captain.

76
00:06:23,375 --> 00:06:25,916
However. The Izumo Plan,
to escape the earth

77
00:06:26,000 --> 00:06:28,125
and resettle in space,
has been shelved.

78
00:06:28,208 --> 00:06:30,291
[CROWD gasping]

79
00:06:30,375 --> 00:06:32,166
[OKITA]
I'll explain your assignment.

80
00:06:32,250 --> 00:06:35,208
But first there's something
I want to show you.

81
00:06:35,291 --> 00:06:37,625
The following, is a video
message we recovered

82
00:06:37,708 --> 00:06:41,458
from an interstellar vessel
as part of Operation M.

83
00:06:41,541 --> 00:06:45,375
[STARSHA] I am Starsha
of the planet Iscandar.

84
00:06:45,458 --> 00:06:46,541
Is that--?

85
00:06:46,625 --> 00:06:47,916
[STARSHA]
Your world as you know it

86
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:49,416
is on the verge of ruin,

87
00:06:49,500 --> 00:06:53,125
due to the relentless
attacks of the Gamilans.

88
00:06:53,208 --> 00:06:54,666
The Gamilans.

89
00:06:54,750 --> 00:06:56,500
[STARSHA]
I learned of this one year ago,

90
00:06:56,583 --> 00:06:58,708
and dispatched
my sister, Yurisha,

91
00:06:58,791 --> 00:07:01,250
to Earth to bring you
plans for a technology

92
00:07:01,333 --> 00:07:04,833
we call the Dimensional
Wave Motion Engine.

93
00:07:04,916 --> 00:07:07,500
Looks like the vessel
we saw on Mars.

94
00:07:07,583 --> 00:07:09,708
[STARSHA] If you can
understand these plans

95
00:07:09,791 --> 00:07:11,833
and successfully
build your own ship,

96
00:07:11,916 --> 00:07:15,083
then come to Iscandar.

97
00:07:15,166 --> 00:07:17,166
On our planet we have
engineered a system

98
00:07:17,250 --> 00:07:19,458
that can cleanse
the Gamilan pollution,

99
00:07:19,541 --> 00:07:22,166
and restore your home world
to its former state.

100
00:07:22,250 --> 00:07:23,166
No way!

101
00:07:23,250 --> 00:07:24,791
You think that's even possible?

102
00:07:24,875 --> 00:07:27,083
[STARSHA] Unfortunately, I can
no longer take this system

103
00:07:27,166 --> 00:07:30,458
to Earth myself. The journey
will have to be yours.

104
00:07:30,541 --> 00:07:32,958
So that's her? The Iscandarian?

105
00:07:33,041 --> 00:07:35,166
Wow, she's beautiful.

106
00:07:35,250 --> 00:07:36,875
[STARSHA]
Now, along with this message,

107
00:07:36,958 --> 00:07:39,333
I have sent you
the Wave Motion Core,

108
00:07:39,416 --> 00:07:43,083
the activation device for the
Dimensional Wave Motion Engine,

109
00:07:43,166 --> 00:07:45,916
which I entrusted to
my other sister, Sasha.

110
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:48,583
I believe you will
overcome unknown dangers

111
00:07:48,666 --> 00:07:50,625
and reach my planet, Earthlings.

112
00:07:50,708 --> 00:07:52,750
I believe you will
find salvation.

113
00:07:52,833 --> 00:07:57,458
I am Starsha of Iscandar,
and I believe in you.

114
00:07:57,541 --> 00:07:58,916
One year ago,

115
00:07:59,000 --> 00:08:01,750
Earth received technological
cooperation from Iscandar,

116
00:08:01,833 --> 00:08:03,458
just as she said.

117
00:08:03,541 --> 00:08:05,958
We poured everything into this,
and we've now completed

118
00:08:06,041 --> 00:08:09,208
a spaceship capable
of interstellar flight.

119
00:08:09,291 --> 00:08:13,125
That tech must be incredible.
I had no idea.

120
00:08:13,208 --> 00:08:16,083
That ship's name:
<i>Yamato</i> !

121
00:08:16,166 --> 00:08:18,125
[CROWD murmuring]

122
00:08:18,208 --> 00:08:19,458
<i>Yamato</i> ?

123
00:08:19,541 --> 00:08:21,333
[OKITA]
She also sent us coordinates.

124
00:08:21,416 --> 00:08:22,750
According to the capsule,

125
00:08:22,833 --> 00:08:26,666
Iscandar is 168,000
light-years from Earth.

126
00:08:26,750 --> 00:08:29,125
In the Large
Magellanic Cloud galaxy.

127
00:08:29,208 --> 00:08:33,166
This journey, 336,000
light-years in total,

128
00:08:33,250 --> 00:08:35,875
is farther than mankind
ever dreamed possible.

129
00:08:35,958 --> 00:08:38,166
And of course there's risk.

130
00:08:38,250 --> 00:08:39,958
I won't force you to come.

131
00:08:40,041 --> 00:08:43,333
Any who wish to
stay here may do so.

132
00:08:43,416 --> 00:08:44,833
You have until
we launch tomorrow

133
00:08:44,916 --> 00:08:47,375
at 0600 hours. So think hard.

134
00:08:47,458 --> 00:08:49,416
I'll assume those
who don't report by then

135
00:08:49,500 --> 00:08:52,583
have chosen to stay.
That will be all.

136
00:08:56,166 --> 00:08:58,875
It's a real shame
Yamamoto is dead.

137
00:08:58,958 --> 00:09:00,166
He'd love this.

138
00:09:00,250 --> 00:09:02,125
Shut up.

139
00:09:04,416 --> 00:09:06,291
Onto personnel.
The following officers

140
00:09:06,375 --> 00:09:08,625
will be in charge
of each division.

141
00:09:08,708 --> 00:09:12,500
Engineering:
Hikozaemon Tokugawa.

142
00:09:12,583 --> 00:09:15,583
Technology Division:
Shiro Sanada.

143
00:09:15,666 --> 00:09:17,541
Lieutenant Commander Sanada
will also serve

144
00:09:17,625 --> 00:09:19,708
as the <i>Yamato</i> 's
second-in-command.

145
00:09:19,791 --> 00:09:24,000
Next division is Tactical.
Susumu Kodai.

146
00:09:24,083 --> 00:09:25,833
[KODAI gasp]

147
00:09:25,916 --> 00:09:27,916
Whoa! Seriously?

148
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:29,791
He's younger than me!

149
00:09:29,875 --> 00:09:33,000
[MORI]
Navigation: Daisuke Shima.

150
00:09:35,375 --> 00:09:36,958
[doorbell buzzes]

151
00:09:37,041 --> 00:09:38,416
[HIJIKATA]
I'm coming in.

152
00:09:41,250 --> 00:09:43,416
[OKITA]
I know what you're going to say.

153
00:09:43,500 --> 00:09:45,416
[HIJIKATA]
Then that makes this easy.

154
00:09:45,500 --> 00:09:47,500
So you're dead-set on going?

155
00:09:47,583 --> 00:09:48,958
Yes.

156
00:09:49,041 --> 00:09:50,666
Despite your condition?

157
00:09:50,750 --> 00:09:52,875
I may be old, but I'm not blind.

158
00:09:52,958 --> 00:09:56,333
How many years have we
known each other now, Juuzo?

159
00:09:56,416 --> 00:09:59,458
Let me go instead.
That takes courage, too.

160
00:09:59,541 --> 00:10:02,375
[OKITA] This voyage
of 168,000 light-years,

161
00:10:02,458 --> 00:10:05,750
may take every bit
of life that I have left.

162
00:10:05,833 --> 00:10:08,333
But I will lead my crew.

163
00:10:08,416 --> 00:10:12,166
And, I will return.

164
00:10:12,250 --> 00:10:16,583
Understood. I won't argue.
Not with a wall.

165
00:10:16,666 --> 00:10:19,625
Take care of Earth.
Give 'em hell.

166
00:10:30,541 --> 00:10:35,500
♪

167
00:10:49,208 --> 00:10:51,958
[ambulance siren blaring]

168
00:10:52,041 --> 00:10:58,750
[bell dings]

169
00:11:03,166 --> 00:11:06,291
So, I hear you'll be
serving on the <i>Yamato</i> , too.

170
00:11:06,375 --> 00:11:10,291
I requested pilot. I want to
be in the wing like my brother.

171
00:11:10,375 --> 00:11:12,208
Well, I'm sorry,
but you're going to be

172
00:11:12,291 --> 00:11:14,166
assigned to accounting.

173
00:11:26,708 --> 00:11:28,083
[scissors snip]

174
00:11:29,375 --> 00:11:31,333
[HIKOSHICHI]
You don't have to go, Dad.

175
00:11:31,416 --> 00:11:34,458
[KIKUKO]
You're retiring in two months!

176
00:11:34,541 --> 00:11:37,750
He asked me to go and take care
of this new engine for him.

177
00:11:37,833 --> 00:11:40,041
That's all the reason I need.

178
00:11:40,125 --> 00:11:41,375
[TASUKE]
Well, it's time, Aiko.

179
00:11:41,458 --> 00:11:44,333
Say goodbye to
your grandpa, okay?

180
00:11:44,416 --> 00:11:45,375
[AIKO]
Grandpa!

181
00:11:45,458 --> 00:11:47,000
Oh, come here, sweetheart.

182
00:11:47,083 --> 00:11:48,625
[chuckles]
I'll be back.

183
00:11:48,708 --> 00:11:51,375
Not even light-years
could keep me from you.

184
00:11:51,458 --> 00:11:52,916
[FEMALE STATION ANNOUNCEMENT 2A]
All embarking personnel,

185
00:11:53,000 --> 00:11:54,958
please have your
identification ready...

186
00:11:55,041 --> 00:11:57,458
[JIRO]
Daisuke!

187
00:11:57,541 --> 00:12:00,750
Jiro! Hey, what's the matter?

188
00:12:00,833 --> 00:12:03,875
Mom asked me
to give this to you.

189
00:12:03,958 --> 00:12:06,166
She said she forgot
to give it to Dad,

190
00:12:06,250 --> 00:12:09,333
so she wanted to make sure
that you have it for good luck.

191
00:12:09,416 --> 00:12:10,791
[SHIMA]
I see.

192
00:12:10,875 --> 00:12:13,875
She worries way too much.
But that's Mom.

193
00:12:13,958 --> 00:12:15,291
Well, don't <i>you</i> worry.

194
00:12:15,375 --> 00:12:17,333
I'm making it back
no matter what.

195
00:12:17,416 --> 00:12:19,958
So you just take good care
of Mom until then.

196
00:12:20,041 --> 00:12:21,166
You promise?

197
00:12:21,250 --> 00:12:22,958
[JIRO]
Mhmm.

198
00:12:25,083 --> 00:12:27,083
Rioting continues day
and night in District Six,

199
00:12:27,166 --> 00:12:29,166
while in District Seven the
Management Center Building

200
00:12:29,250 --> 00:12:30,708
has been leveled by a bomb,

201
00:12:30,791 --> 00:12:33,416
with rioters
claiming responsibility.

202
00:12:33,500 --> 00:12:35,750
The Far East Sector government
is asking all citizens

203
00:12:35,833 --> 00:12:38,375
to remain calm while
resources can be distrib--

204
00:12:42,833 --> 00:12:45,625
I'm coming back. You'll see.

205
00:12:47,500 --> 00:12:49,166
I'm so worried I'm nauseous.

206
00:12:49,250 --> 00:12:51,416
The ship's OMCS should
be perfectly capable

207
00:12:51,500 --> 00:12:53,250
of producing alcohol, sir.

208
00:12:53,333 --> 00:12:54,833
No, for Mew!

209
00:12:54,916 --> 00:12:57,000
Oh, I'm sure she'll be fine.

210
00:13:10,666 --> 00:13:12,041
[MALE LOADING OPERATOR 2A]
Inspections completed.

211
00:13:12,125 --> 00:13:14,291
All systems go.

212
00:13:14,375 --> 00:13:16,083
[MALE LOADING OPERATOR 2B]
Direct all personnel transports

213
00:13:16,166 --> 00:13:17,791
to Deck Three for boarding.

214
00:13:17,875 --> 00:13:19,208
[MALE LOADING OPERATOR 2A]
Maintenance and repair teams,

215
00:13:19,291 --> 00:13:21,291
you are clear
to load the planes.

216
00:13:22,333 --> 00:13:23,583
[REPAIRMAN 2A]
I guess this one goes

217
00:13:23,666 --> 00:13:26,166
to the autopilot room, right?

218
00:13:26,250 --> 00:13:27,750
[ENOMOTO]
Hm?

219
00:13:31,625 --> 00:13:33,125
[ENOMOTO chuckles]

220
00:13:34,458 --> 00:13:35,708
[MALE LOADING OPERATOR 2B]
All reporting personnel...

221
00:13:35,791 --> 00:13:37,416
What's this?

222
00:13:37,500 --> 00:13:38,791
[MALE LOADING OPERATOR 2B]
...and check in for onboard

223
00:13:38,875 --> 00:13:41,750
orientation and
receipt of uniforms.

224
00:13:41,833 --> 00:13:43,666
All crewmembers
have reported, sir.

225
00:13:43,750 --> 00:13:45,541
No one chose to stay.

226
00:13:45,625 --> 00:13:49,791
[OKITA] Mm. So all that's
left now is the engine.

227
00:13:49,875 --> 00:13:51,958
[SANADA] This is it,
the Wave Motion Core.

228
00:13:52,041 --> 00:13:53,375
And that's the last
part we need

229
00:13:53,458 --> 00:13:55,375
to get her up and running, huh?

230
00:14:08,958 --> 00:14:11,875
[SANADA]
Engine response is confirmed.

231
00:14:11,958 --> 00:14:14,333
[TOKUGAWA] Does that mean
we can start her now?

232
00:14:14,416 --> 00:14:15,958
[SANADA]
No. That's going to take

233
00:14:16,041 --> 00:14:17,916
more power than we have
at our disposal.

234
00:14:18,000 --> 00:14:20,666
That's kind of mean of
our goddess, don't you think?

235
00:14:20,750 --> 00:14:22,125
[FEMALE ANNOUNCEMENT VOICE 1A]
All personnel are to change

236
00:14:22,208 --> 00:14:25,041
into their crew uniforms
immediately after checking in.

237
00:14:25,125 --> 00:14:26,625
Follow your superior's orders

238
00:14:26,708 --> 00:14:29,250
and remain on standby
at your station.

239
00:14:29,333 --> 00:14:31,083
[KATO]
So you're in charge of Tactical.

240
00:14:31,166 --> 00:14:32,666
[FEMALE ANNOUNCEMENT VOICE 1A]
All personnel are to change

241
00:14:32,750 --> 00:14:34,750
into their crew uniforms
immediately after checking in.

242
00:14:34,833 --> 00:14:36,166
Follow your superior's orders

243
00:14:36,250 --> 00:14:37,583
and remain on standby
at your station.

244
00:14:37,666 --> 00:14:39,625
Well, that makes you
my commanding officer now.

245
00:14:39,708 --> 00:14:41,458
So, I'll obey your orders.

246
00:14:41,541 --> 00:14:43,541
That said, if you
ever issue a command

247
00:14:43,625 --> 00:14:46,166
that gets my men
killed for nothing...

248
00:14:46,250 --> 00:14:48,625
...then trust me,
you'll pay for it.

249
00:14:48,708 --> 00:14:51,125
You don't have to
worry about that.

250
00:14:51,208 --> 00:14:53,208
[KATO]
We're all counting on you.

251
00:14:57,791 --> 00:15:00,666
I'll make it.
I'm coming home for sure.

252
00:15:00,750 --> 00:15:02,416
--[digital beep]
--[gasps]

253
00:15:05,416 --> 00:15:08,375
[gasps] I didn't realize
you were part of the crew.

254
00:15:08,458 --> 00:15:11,500
Yes. You're running Tactical.
Kodai, right?

255
00:15:11,583 --> 00:15:14,250
Lieutenant Yuki Mori,
Chief Operations Officer.

256
00:15:14,333 --> 00:15:15,375
Welcome aboard.

257
00:15:15,458 --> 00:15:17,333
So where's our Captain?

258
00:15:17,416 --> 00:15:18,416
[knock, knock]

259
00:15:18,500 --> 00:15:19,833
Who is it?

260
00:15:19,916 --> 00:15:21,416
[KODAI]
Susumu Kodai, sir.

261
00:15:21,500 --> 00:15:22,625
Come in.

262
00:15:22,708 --> 00:15:24,166
[KODAI]
Thank you.

263
00:15:27,875 --> 00:15:29,250
What is it?

264
00:15:29,333 --> 00:15:33,000
Well, it's about my role
as Chief Tactical Officer.

265
00:15:33,083 --> 00:15:34,875
I just don't...

266
00:15:36,500 --> 00:15:38,291
I don't think
I'm qualified, sir.

267
00:15:38,375 --> 00:15:40,625
[OKITA] Most of our top
candidates for Division Leaders

268
00:15:40,708 --> 00:15:43,041
were making on-site
preparations for the launch,

269
00:15:43,125 --> 00:15:45,000
and were killed
in yesterday's bombing.

270
00:15:45,083 --> 00:15:46,208
[KODAI]
But, sir.

271
00:15:46,291 --> 00:15:47,458
[OKITA] And the soldier
who was supposed to

272
00:15:47,541 --> 00:15:49,375
sit in your chair, Lieutenant.

273
00:15:49,458 --> 00:15:51,708
Well, I'm responsible
for his death, too.

274
00:15:51,791 --> 00:15:53,000
[KODAI gasps]

275
00:15:53,083 --> 00:15:56,125
[OKITA] Mamoru Kodai,
your older brother.

276
00:15:56,208 --> 00:15:57,791
[KODAI gasps]

277
00:15:57,875 --> 00:16:00,333
I've examined your
service record myself.

278
00:16:00,416 --> 00:16:03,375
And I've decided you're more
than capable of the position,

279
00:16:03,458 --> 00:16:05,750
or at least worthy
of the chance.

280
00:16:05,833 --> 00:16:09,916
From now on, it's up to you
to prove me right.

281
00:16:12,333 --> 00:16:15,458
What's his problem, anyway?
He's got no manners.

282
00:16:15,541 --> 00:16:17,083
[SHIMA]
Hey!

283
00:16:17,166 --> 00:16:18,416
This is the First Bridge, huh?

284
00:16:18,500 --> 00:16:20,000
It's really something.

285
00:16:20,083 --> 00:16:23,083
I'm Lieutenant Daisuke Shima,
our Chief Navigation Officer.

286
00:16:23,166 --> 00:16:24,750
We've met before, haven't we?

287
00:16:24,833 --> 00:16:26,666
The captain's upstairs, okay!

288
00:16:26,750 --> 00:16:28,125
[SHIMA]
Uh--

289
00:16:31,125 --> 00:16:33,208
Oh. Hey, Kodai.

290
00:16:35,166 --> 00:16:38,125
What's wrong?
Did something happen?

291
00:16:38,208 --> 00:16:41,000
No, it's nothing.
Don't worry, I'm fine.

292
00:16:44,416 --> 00:16:45,958
So this is the
first bridge crew.

293
00:16:46,041 --> 00:16:47,500
I'm Lieutenant Commander Sanada.

294
00:16:47,583 --> 00:16:48,750
Is everyone ready?

295
00:16:48,833 --> 00:16:49,875
[ALL]
Yes, sir.

296
00:16:49,958 --> 00:16:52,708
[siren blaring]

297
00:16:52,791 --> 00:16:55,000
To your stations, on the
double-- This is no drill.

298
00:16:55,083 --> 00:16:56,583
[ALL]
Yes, sir.

299
00:16:59,375 --> 00:17:01,958
Confirm the situation
with Command.

300
00:17:02,041 --> 00:17:03,500
Receiving message now, sir.

301
00:17:03,583 --> 00:17:06,500
Interplanetary ballistic missile
sited on path to Earth.

302
00:17:06,583 --> 00:17:08,375
Assessed target.
[gasps]

303
00:17:08,458 --> 00:17:10,500
Battleship <i>Yamato</i> !

304
00:17:10,583 --> 00:17:12,666
But we can't launch yet, can we?

305
00:17:12,750 --> 00:17:14,875
[ANALYZER] Negative.
Significantly more energy

306
00:17:14,958 --> 00:17:17,333
required to reach
escape velocity.

307
00:17:17,416 --> 00:17:19,333
The problem is where
we get that energy,

308
00:17:19,416 --> 00:17:21,500
our grid is completely taxed.

309
00:17:21,583 --> 00:17:22,708
Oh, man.

310
00:17:22,791 --> 00:17:24,291
But we are gonna
make it, right, sir?

311
00:17:24,375 --> 00:17:26,000
[OKITA]
Stay focused!

312
00:17:29,833 --> 00:17:33,833
Go Comms. Get command
on the line, main screen.

313
00:17:33,916 --> 00:17:35,625
Oh. Hello, Admiral.

314
00:17:35,708 --> 00:17:38,708
We making any progress with
the power supply, Director?

315
00:17:38,791 --> 00:17:41,291
We'll see. We've begun
routing all power from

316
00:17:41,375 --> 00:17:44,458
the Far East Sector
into the <i>Yamato</i> 's main line.

317
00:17:44,541 --> 00:17:46,750
But since we had no time
to test the activator

318
00:17:46,833 --> 00:17:49,208
we have no way to know
if it's enough--

319
00:17:49,291 --> 00:17:51,333
[OKITA]
Mmmm.

320
00:17:51,416 --> 00:17:52,916
[siren blares]

321
00:17:53,000 --> 00:17:54,541
Power in Far East
Sector is down.

322
00:17:54,625 --> 00:17:56,125
All districts!

323
00:17:56,208 --> 00:17:57,750
Switch to backup generators!

324
00:17:57,833 --> 00:17:59,083
[MALE UNCF CONTROLLER 2A]
Switch to backup, confirmed.

325
00:17:59,166 --> 00:18:00,750
If that's not enough power
we'll have to call off

326
00:18:00,833 --> 00:18:03,041
the launch, and she'll be
a sitting duck out there.

327
00:18:03,125 --> 00:18:04,291
[MALE UNCF CONTROLLER 2E]
Director,

328
00:18:04,375 --> 00:18:05,750
you'll want to see this, sir.

329
00:18:07,125 --> 00:18:08,541
[YABU]
Lieutenant, look!

330
00:18:08,625 --> 00:18:10,708
I'll be.

331
00:18:10,791 --> 00:18:12,916
[MALE UNCF CONTROLLER 2E]
North America, Africa, Eurasia,

332
00:18:13,000 --> 00:18:14,791
all sectors are rerouting power!

333
00:18:14,875 --> 00:18:16,416
The whole world
is answering the call,

334
00:18:16,500 --> 00:18:18,750
giving the ship every
kilowatt they can spare.

335
00:18:18,833 --> 00:18:20,250
How's it look?

336
00:18:20,333 --> 00:18:23,166
[YAMAZAKI] It worked, Chief.
We can fire her up.

337
00:18:23,250 --> 00:18:26,625
[OKITA] Mm!
Activate Wave Motion Engine!

338
00:18:26,708 --> 00:18:29,291
[TOKUGAWA] Activating now.
Connecting flywheel.

339
00:18:29,375 --> 00:18:32,875
Pressure rising.
Ninety. Ninety-six.

340
00:18:32,958 --> 00:18:34,208
One hundred percent.

341
00:18:34,291 --> 00:18:36,208
Energy charge at 120!

342
00:18:36,291 --> 00:18:38,750
Wave Motion Engine live.
RPMs looking good.

343
00:18:38,833 --> 00:18:40,208
Here we go!

344
00:18:50,000 --> 00:18:52,500
[MORI] Interplanetary
ballistic missile spotted!

345
00:18:52,583 --> 00:18:56,000
Straighten the ship for launch!
Remove camouflage!

346
00:19:08,625 --> 00:19:09,875
[KODAI]
What is this?

347
00:19:09,958 --> 00:19:11,541
[ANALYZER] Prototype built
within existing vessel,

348
00:19:11,625 --> 00:19:13,958
providing camouflage
to deceive enemy.

349
00:19:14,041 --> 00:19:16,333
Camouflage. That explains it--

350
00:19:16,416 --> 00:19:19,166
the sunken battleship
in that dried sea bed!

351
00:19:19,250 --> 00:19:22,166
Yes, Lieutenant.
We're on board her now.

352
00:19:22,250 --> 00:19:25,000
The Space Battleship <i>Yamato</i> !

353
00:19:27,500 --> 00:19:29,875
If we want her to see space,
we need to blow that missile

354
00:19:29,958 --> 00:19:33,791
out of the sky.
Prepare to fire the cannons!

355
00:19:33,875 --> 00:19:35,916
Prepare the main cannons.
Let's go!

356
00:19:36,000 --> 00:19:37,833
[MALE OFFICER 2D]
Man your positions!

357
00:19:41,416 --> 00:19:44,083
Open the throttle!
Let's get her airborne!

358
00:19:44,166 --> 00:19:46,875
[SHIMA] Aye-aye, Captain!
Launching <i>Yamato</i> now!

359
00:19:46,958 --> 00:19:56,958
♪

360
00:20:16,750 --> 00:20:17,958
Shock cannons live.

361
00:20:18,041 --> 00:20:19,958
The engine has charged them
to maximum power.

362
00:20:20,041 --> 00:20:21,208
Target is sighted.

363
00:20:21,291 --> 00:20:23,166
Engage the automatic tracking.

364
00:20:23,250 --> 00:20:24,958
[NANBU]
Automatic tracking engaged.

365
00:20:41,291 --> 00:20:42,375
Locking on target.

366
00:20:42,458 --> 00:20:46,333
Correcting for errors,
minus 1.3.

367
00:20:46,416 --> 00:20:47,291
[KODAI]
Target lock.

368
00:20:47,375 --> 00:20:49,041
Open fire, full bore!

369
00:20:49,125 --> 00:20:50,500
Fire!

370
00:21:05,666 --> 00:21:07,791
[MALE UNCF CONTROLLER 2A] Power
coming back on line, sir.

371
00:21:07,875 --> 00:21:09,666
[SERIZAWA, TODO gasp]

372
00:21:09,750 --> 00:21:11,166
Where's the <i>Yamato</i> ?

373
00:21:11,250 --> 00:21:14,166
If that missile struck,
it may have been incinerated.

374
00:21:22,208 --> 00:21:23,125
[MALE UNCF CONTROLLER 2A]
No damage, sir!

375
00:21:23,208 --> 00:21:24,625
The <i>Yamato</i> is fine!

376
00:21:44,125 --> 00:21:46,541
[SANADA]
Releasing Wave Motion Shields.

377
00:21:46,625 --> 00:21:48,375
That didn't even
leave a scratch.

378
00:21:48,458 --> 00:21:49,958
[OTA exhales]

379
00:21:51,083 --> 00:21:53,208
Kodai.

380
00:21:53,291 --> 00:21:54,833
Yes, sir?

381
00:21:54,916 --> 00:21:57,500
That was well done.

382
00:21:57,583 --> 00:21:59,250
[SHIMA]
Would it kill you to smile?

383
00:24:13,000 --> 00:24:14,791
[OKITA]
The time has come to embark,

384
00:24:14,875 --> 00:24:17,208
and the Space Battleship
<i>Yamato</i> sets course

385
00:24:17,291 --> 00:24:19,333
for Iscandar,
the planet of hope.

386
00:24:19,416 --> 00:24:21,583
This vessel and her crew
are the only ones

387
00:24:21,666 --> 00:24:25,083
who can journey across the stars
and save our civilization.

388
00:24:25,166 --> 00:24:26,500
But we don't even
fully understand

389
00:24:26,583 --> 00:24:28,041
the new power we hold.

390
00:24:28,125 --> 00:24:30,791
Now the <i>Yamato</i> 's true
strength will be revealed.

391
00:24:30,875 --> 00:24:32,750
Is it too much for us?

392
00:24:32,833 --> 00:24:35,625
Next time: "Escape from
the Jupiter Sphere."

393
00:24:35,708 --> 00:24:40,875
There are 364 days left
before humanity becomes extinct.

